g.text: 1.1 Find the Sub Tree Size for each node Using DFS
* If each sub-tree has the same size, the first edge is Heavy Edge
1.2 Distinguish between heavy edge and light edge
Heavy Edge is the edge connecting the child node with the largest sub-tree size.
1.3 Find the interval for each node Using ETT
* The start number of the Node is the number of the Edge
that connects the parent Node and itself.
2.1 Update Max segment trees on a per-interval basis
* Change DFS order to Heavy Edge order
2.2 Processing of interval calculations according to circumstances
-- Example 1(when two nodes are in the same Heavy Edge group)
-- Example 2(when two nodes are in different groups)
The Edge with Node 8 and 11 connected is 9 and 10.
* In other words Connected Edge = S[8] + 1 ~ S[11] = 9~10
[1] Find a node with a smaller sub-tree size among
the Root nodes of two node groups.
> Root node of Node 3 Group = Node 1
> Root node of Node 10 Group = Node 7
[1] Calculate the interval between the two nodes.
[3] Compare whether the node after crossing the Light Edge and
the node that previously had a large sub-tree size are in the same group.
* Calculate including the Light Edge connected to the Root Node in the group.
Light Edge connected to the Root Node = S[7] = 7
Node 1 and Node 3 belong to the same group.
* Repeat [1]~[3] until two nodes belong to the same group.
[4] Calculate the interval between the two nodes.
